<br>
He had been born the day the realm came about, his house of the first circle of houses in the realm; it was a long and proud past.  Yet, it was a past.  The halls had grown quiet and webs covered many places.  The servants had grown old and not been replaced.  Many had died or left to other houses for strength and companionship, still others had just faded from the world.  When he returned the Conclave was all but a memory and a rumor to many in this land.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
“It is time” he thought.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> He steps from the halls and looks back a moment, his lips start to whisper the incantation, his voice growing louder with each moment, until at last it is a roar.  The fire starts in the entrance and sweeps through the halls at a dizzying speed, ravenous flames lick and consume.  It takes two days for the flames to finish their job, the Halls of the Damned lay in ashes.<br>
<br>
Kazanti turns and addresses the few whom have stayed and the crowd that had gathered.  </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
From ashes we rise again.  The darkness will stir harsh about our walls again; the name of the Damned shall stand for something again in these realms.  The foundation shall be pride in our past and an old history.  We do not forget those whom have went before nor dishonor the earned reputation they have gathered for us.  Our past is who we are.  The day has come for a new house to be built though, one of equaled honor and respect.  We are of this community and continue to be such.  Let the Conclave of the Damned stir the shadows again.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> He turns and starts to direct the workmen gathered as they build the halls that will hold the Conclave of the Damned. </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> OOC </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
There have been rumors that the Conclave is no more, and I have passed.  Well they have been wrong.  I rebuild this old house once more and I do something I have never done before.  In the past we did not openly recruit, but waited for those wishing to join to seek us out.  Well I’m going to send out a one time only recruitment.<br>
<br>
I seek <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>1 ((edit: have one key spot left to fill)) </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> strong and independent individual wishing to help remake this guild in the vision we have long sought.  The goal is simple we have three priorities 1) Fun 2) Role-Play 3) Community.  The guild will have a strong sense of family and community, our focus and priority is to build a stronger RP community on our server, by interacting with the public often and by holding small open events.  We will also be very politically active, seeking out other houses, guilds and organizations, openly opposing neutral and good RPers.  <br>
<br>
It is time many of us look back to what we wanted when we came here, to the environment we dreamed we could have and did something to hold onto that dream.  Apathy has set on this server harsh and many speak only of what is unable to happen.  I for one am looking for those who still have the dream and are willing to put the time and effort into spreading that dream once again.<br>
<br>
If this interests you send me an E-Mail at <!--EZCODE MAIL START--><a href="mailto:conclaveofthedamned@yahoo.com"> conclaveofthedamned@yahoo.com</a><!--EZCODE MAIL END-->  Include<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> Name:  Class:  Race:  Alignment:  Brief description of character:  and Why you are interested.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
